definitions.definition: To challenge (an incumbent sitting politician ) for their political party 's nomination to run for re-election , through running a challenger campaign in a primary election , especially one that is more ideologically extreme .
To take part in a primary election .

main_definition: ( US , politics , transitive , intransitive ) To challenge (an incumbent sitting politician ) for their political party 's nomination to run for re-election , through running a challenger campaign in a primary election , especially one that is more ideologically extreme .
secondary_definitions: ( US , intransitive , transitive ) To take part in a primary election .
